@@ -0,0 +1,122 @@
+# EveJS Universe Market Mirror
+
+This utility builds an EveJS seed market from EVE Online's public ESI market feed. It preserves the live market's location pattern: an item is seeded at an NPC station only when the snapshot saw a public order for that item at that exact station.
+
+It does **not** copy every item into every station. It also does not overwrite player-created market orders, order events, or price history.
+
+## What it mirrors
+
+- Public regional sell and buy orders from all ESI regions.
+- Exact NPC station, item type, and order side.
+- Remaining order volume, summed per station/item/side to match EveJS's seed schema.
+- All EveJS NPC stations, systems, and regions in the market topology tables.
+
+Orders whose location is not an NPC station in the installed EveJS static data are recorded in the snapshot report and omitted. This normally includes Upwell structures. Those markets require authenticated structure-market access and are intentionally outside the default safety-focused workflow.
+
+## Price modes
+
+Set `pricePolicy.mode` in the configuration file:
+
+- `clamped_live` (recommended): uses the station's volume-weighted live price, limited to a configurable band around a reference price. The included example uses 0.5x to 2.0x.
+- `live`: uses the station's volume-weighted live price without normalization.
+- `reference`: uses ESI's average/adjusted reference price, with a buy/sell spread.
+- `static_base`: uses the EveJS/SDE base price, with a buy/sell spread; it falls back to ESI reference and then live price when no useful static base exists.
+
+If both sides exist and the chosen policy would cross them, the utility adjusts them so the buy price remains below the sell price.
+
+## Requirements
+
+- EveJS v0.12.2 with its market server installed.
+- The Node.js dependencies already installed by EveJS.
+- Internet access to `esi.evetech.net`.
+- A descriptive `User-Agent` containing a project name and contact method.
+
+## Client order compatibility
+
+Real market volumes can aggregate above the legacy client's 32-bit row-list limit. This package includes the v0.12.2/build-3396210 compatibility installer used for the verified run:
+
+```powershell
+powershell -NoProfile -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File ".\compatibility\Install-MarketOrderRowListFix.ps1" -ServerRoot "D:\Games\EveJS" -CheckOnly
+powershell -NoProfile -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File ".\compatibility\Install-MarketOrderRowListFix.ps1" -ServerRoot "D:\Games\EveJS" -Yes
+```
+
+It verifies the source hash, creates a source backup, installs the TQ-compatible `RowList` encoder, and includes a runtime verifier. Install it before applying a full snapshot unless your EveJS checkout already contains an equivalent fix. The database retains the full quantity; the compatibility encoder limits the per-order value sent to this legacy client to its safe maximum.
+
+## Configure
+
+Copy `config.example.json` to `config.local.json` and edit `esi.userAgent`. The default configuration uses `clamped_live` pricing.
+
+## Build a snapshot
+
+From this directory:
+
+```powershell
+.\Update-UniverseMarket.ps1 -Action Snapshot -ServerRoot "D:\Games\EveJS" -Config ".\config.local.json"
+```
+
+For a trial run limited to The Forge:
+
+```powershell
+node .\market-universe-mirror.js snapshot --server-root "D:\Games\EveJS" --config ".\config.local.json" --region 10000002
+```
+
+The snapshot stage is read-only with respect to the live market database. It stores:
+
+- A compact SQLite plan containing the exact rows that would be applied.
+- Raw ESI response pages and HTTP metadata for auditing.
+- Counts of accepted orders and orders skipped because their location or type is unknown locally.
+
+## Apply a snapshot
+
+Close the EVE client and stop both the EveJS game server and market server. The apply command refuses to run while their known ports are open.
+
+```powershell
+.\Update-UniverseMarket.ps1 -Action Apply -ServerRoot "D:\Games\EveJS" -Config ".\config.local.json" -Snapshot "C:\path\to\market-snapshot.sqlite"
+```
+
+Before changing the database, the utility copies the SQLite database family to:
+
+```text
+<EveJS>\backups\x-eve-universe-market\<timestamp>
+```
+
+The apply stage replaces only EveJS's generated seed stock and generated seed buy orders, rebuilds station/system/region summaries, and writes its settings and snapshot counts to the market manifest.
+
+Restart the market server first, then the EveJS game server.
+
+## Verify
+
+```powershell
+.\Update-UniverseMarket.ps1 -Action Doctor -ServerRoot "D:\Games\EveJS"
+```
+
+The result should show a healthy SQLite database plus nonzero station, system, region, sell-seed, and buy-seed counts.
+
+## Sharing a reproducible update
+
+When sharing reproducible results, include:
+
+- EveJS version and client build.
+- Snapshot creation time and ESI compatibility date.
+- Price mode and clamp/spread settings.
+- Regions/pages/orders processed.
+- Accepted station/item/side combinations and skipped unknown locations.
+- The generated manifest and the tool version or commit.
+- Whether the market-order `RowList` compatibility fix was installed.
+
+Do not distribute the full raw market cache by default; it is large and quickly becomes stale. Share the configuration, report, and code so another administrator can reproduce the snapshot.
+
+## Public data limitations
+
+The public regional ESI endpoint is the correct source for public NPC-station availability and exact `location_id` values. Private or access-controlled structure markets require an authenticated character, a known structure ID, docking access, and the structure-market scope. The mirror reports rather than guesses those locations.
+
+The tool respects ESI pagination, cache metadata, `Retry-After`, and market-specific rate-limit headers. A full public snapshot is designed to be run periodically, not continuously.
+
+## Official references
+
+- ESI overview and compatibility dates: https://developers.eveonline.com/docs/services/esi/overview/
+- ESI rate limiting: https://developers.eveonline.com/docs/services/esi/rate-limiting/
+- ESI pagination: https://developers.eveonline.com/docs/services/esi/pagination/x-pages/
+- ESI best practices: https://developers.eveonline.com/docs/services/esi/best-practices/
+- Structure markets: https://docs.esi.evetech.net/docs/scenarios/structure_markets.html
+- Resolving structure IDs: https://docs.esi.evetech.net/docs/scenarios/resolve_structure_ids.html
